VI was born in a family full of colors.
p12
aVMy father is the son of a maid
p13
aVfrom whom he inherited an intense dark chocolate tone.
p14
aVHe was adopted by those who I know as my grandparents.
p15
aVThe matriarch, my grandma,
p16
aVhas a porcelain skin and cotton-like hair.
p17
aVMy grandpa was somewhere between a vanilla and strawberry yogurt tone,
p18
aVlike my uncle and my cousin.
p19
aVMy mother is a cinnamon-skin daughter of a native Brazilian,
p20
aVwith a pinch of hazel and honey,
p21
aVand a man [who is] a mix of coffee with milk,
p22
aVbut with a lot of coffee.
p23
aVShe has two sisters.
p24
aVOne in a toasted-peanut skin
p25
aVand the other,
p26
aValso adopted,
p27
aVmore on the beige side,
p28
aVlike a pancake.
p29
aa(lp30
V(Laughter)
